{"title":"Deck your bars with festive ReMote colors from WTC, plus new ShiftMounts for Drop Bars","link":"https://bikerumor.com/deck-your-bars-with-festive-remote-colors-from-wtc-plus-new-shiftmounts-for-drop-bars/","date":1638896408000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102047/ReMote_Limited-Green-and-Red_1.jpg\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102047/ReMote_Limited-Green-and-Red_1-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102047/ReMote_Limited-Green-and-Red_1-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102047/ReMote_Limited-Green-and-Red_1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102047/ReMote_Limited-Green-and-Red_1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102047/ReMote_Limited-Green-and-Red_1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102047/ReMote_Limited-Green-and-Red_1.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-280244\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>Even if you don’t plan on dressing up your bike for the holidays, you might be interested in the latest drop from Wolf Tooth Components. Starting today, they will be offering Red and Green versions of their excellent dropper post ReMotes—for a limited time of course.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102052/ReMote_Limited-Green-and-Red_3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102052/ReMote_Limited-Green-and-Red_3.jpg\" alt=\"Wolf Tooth Components red and green remote colors dropper lever\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102052/ReMote_Limited-Green-and-Red_3.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102052/ReMote_Limited-Green-and-Red_3-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102052/ReMote_Limited-Green-and-Red_3-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102052/ReMote_Limited-Green-and-Red_3-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102052/ReMote_Limited-Green-and-Red_3-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>Available in both ReMote and ReMote Light Action, these festive dropper levers are only available with a 22.2mm clamp. However, they can be adapted to work with the other mounting options from WTC with the right hardware. The red and green colors match existing WTC red and green parts and accessories, so you can go all-in on red or green if that’s your thing.</p><p>Apparently, the first time WTC has ever offered a green dropper lever, these are only going to be offered in a limited quantity. Once they’re gone, WTC says they won’t be “back for a while.” Pricing is the same as their standard black options, with both selling for $69.95 each.</p><h2>Drop Bar Shiftmounts&nbsp;<a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102110/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount_MM-31.8mm_3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102110/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount_MM-31.8mm_3.jpg\" alt=\"WTC MTB shifter on dropbar\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102110/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount_MM-31.8mm_3.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102110/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount_MM-31.8mm_3-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102110/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount_MM-31.8mm_3-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102110/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount_MM-31.8mm_3-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102110/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount_MM-31.8mm_3-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></h2><p>Want to add mountain bike shifters to a drop bar? If so, WTC is adding another ShiftMount option to get it done. Paul Components has offered a <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/paul-components-adapts-shifters-to-your-bike-in-two-more-new-ways/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">similar option</a> for years, but only for SRAM.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102101/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount-31.8mm-Clamp.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102101/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount-31.8mm-Clamp.jpg\" alt=\"WTC ShiftMount Shimano SRAM\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102101/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount-31.8mm-Clamp.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102101/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount-31.8mm-Clamp-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102101/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount-31.8mm-Clamp-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102101/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount-31.8mm-Clamp-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102101/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount-31.8mm-Clamp-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>WTC had previously introduced a 22.2mm ShiftMount which was meant for mounting various shifters to flat bars. This new option uses a 31.8mm clamp to allow for MTB shifters on drop bars. The new Wolf Tooth 31.8 Clamp ShiftMounts are available to fit either SRAM MatchMaker/MatchMake X or Shimano I-SPEC EV shifters.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102059/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount-31.8-ISEV-clamp.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102059/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount-31.8-ISEV-clamp.jpg\" alt=\"WTC Shimano MTB shifter on dropbar\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102059/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount-31.8-ISEV-clamp.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102059/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount-31.8-ISEV-clamp-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102059/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount-31.8-ISEV-clamp-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102059/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount-31.8-ISEV-clamp-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102059/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount-31.8-ISEV-clamp-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102103/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount_ISEV-31.8mm_2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102103/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount_ISEV-31.8mm_2.jpg\" alt=\"31.8mm mount for Shimano MTB shifter\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102103/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount_ISEV-31.8mm_2.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102103/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount_ISEV-31.8mm_2-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102103/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount_ISEV-31.8mm_2-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102103/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount_ISEV-31.8mm_2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/07102103/Wolf-Tooth_ShiftMount_ISEV-31.8mm_2-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>Designed for use with the right (rear) shifter, and position the shifter next to the stem for access when you’re riding on top of the bars. Each ShiftMount option sells for $39.95, is made in Minneapolis, and is available now.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=ale&amp;pw=147535&amp;mi=18985&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wolftoothcomponents.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"ugc\"><em>wolftoothcomponents.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"5bbe4af1dfe9d15b7c93b5ccf7ff5b7d878ae5c4d68a899f7e98148e13662824","category":"Cycling"}